## Dalek (Doctor Who episode)

### Overview

For other uses, see [Dalek (disambiguation)](/Dalek_(disambiguation)).

This entry concerns the 2005 episode of [Doctor Who](/Doctor_Who), a British [science fiction television](/Science_fiction_television) programme. It's the sixth installment of the revived [first series](/Doctor_Who_(series_1)), first gracing the airwaves of [BBC One](/BBC_One) on 30 April 2005. This particular episode is notable for marking the grand return of the [Daleks](/Dalek) to the modern era of the show, and also for introducing [Bruno Langley](/Bruno_Langley) as [Adam Mitchell](/Adam_Mitchell_(Doctor_Who)), a temporary [companion](/Companion_(Doctor_Who)).

The narrative unfolds in Utah, in the year 2012. The setting is an underground vault, a morbid collection of alien artifacts amassed by the obscenely wealthy collector, [Henry van Statten](/List_of_Doctor_Who_villains). Within this sterile, oppressive environment, the alien [time traveller](/Time_travel_in_fiction) known only as the [Ninth Doctor](/Ninth_Doctor), portrayed by [Christopher Eccleston](/Christopher_Eccleston), and his companion [Rose Tyler](/Rose_Tyler) (played by [Billie Piper](/Billie_Piper)) stumble upon the bunker's solitary living exhibit: a Dalek. It’s a creature of pure, unadulterated hatred, and it doesn't take long for it to break free, embarking on a mission to eradicate everyone within its reach after a rather convenient self-repair.

